SACTOOLS
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
This is a group of stand-alone tools that act on Seismic Analysis Code (SAC)
formatted files.  This group of tools deals with conversion of SAC files back and
forth between SAC and ASCII files, retrieving header information from SAC files
on the command line, and same basic tasks such as stacking files.

In this README I provide a *very* brief description of the utilities included 
in this repository.  For more details on the use of these utilities see the 
examples in the './examples' directory. The examples directory includes a few
SAC formatted files and some C-shell scripts that can be used to test that the
programs are working.

Author:  Michael Thorne (michael.thorne@utah.edu)
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#


# Codes currently included in the repository:
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
1) amp2sac (amp2sac.f90) - takes a column of amplitude values in ASCII and converts
                           these to SAC format.

2) mavg (mavg.f90) - computes a n-point moving average on a SAC file.

3) rmserror (rmserror.f90 ) - compute RMS error between data and synthetic.

4) sac2xy (sac2xy.f90) - converts a SAC file into an x,y table of time and amplitude.

5) sac2xyfill (sac2xyfill.f90) - same as sac2xy but fills in the positive amplitudes.

6) sachead (sachead.f90) - return the value of a SAC header variable.

7) sacsnr (sacsnr.f90) - compute estimate of signal to noise ratio in SAC file.

8) sacunused (sacunused.f90) - sets 'unused' header variables in SAC files.

9) stacksac (stacksac.f90) - linearly stack some SAC files.

10) stacksacgc (stacksacgc.f90) - takes a group of SAC files and stacks them in 
                                   epicentral distance bins.

11) stacksacaz (stacksacaz.f90) - Stack a group of SAC files in azimuth bins.

12) stalta (stalta.f90) - computes STA/LTA of a SAC file.

13) xy2sac (xy2sac.f90) - convert an x,y table of time and amplitude values into a SAC
                          file.


# Modules included in the repository
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
1) mod_sac_io.f90 - authored by Nicholas Schmerr. Fortran module for reading/
                    writing SAC files

# To Do
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#


# This is just a listing of codes that I already have that I will be adding to
# this repository.  Mostly, this is just for my accounting purposes.
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
1)  mergesac  - merges multiple SAC files into a single file.
2)  padsac    - pads two SAC files with zeros to start and end at the same time.
3)  peaks     - finds peaks in SAC files.
4)  sacmax    - finds maximum/minimum amplitudes (and corresponding times) within a set
                time window in a SAC file.
5)  xcorr     - time domain cross-correlation between SAC files.
6)  convolve  - convolve basic functions with a SAC file.
